ReviewContent: Second bad experience in a month. Sent food back twice.  Came back raw.

Mel-O-Dees Cocktails in El Cerrito is a true gem for those seeking a sophisticated and mature atmosphere. From the moment you step inside, youre greeted with an air of elegance and charm that sets the tone for an unforgettable evening. The crowd exudes a refined energy, creating an ambiance perfect for intimate conversations or simply enjoying a well-crafted cocktail. The bartenders are true artisans, mastering classic concoctions while also innovating with creative new blends. The attention to detail in both the drinks and the decor is impeccable, showcasing a dedication to quality thats second to none. Whether youre a cocktail connoisseur or simply looking for a classy night out, Mel-O-Dees exceeds expectations on every level. A five-star experience thats sure to leave you longing for more.

Friday 1/17/2020 my mom stepdad and friend attended mel-o-dees I arrived 1st alone when I got there I ordered my friend and myself a margarita and opened a TAB I was by myself as I mentioned so my friend arrived and then my mom and stepdad arrived and they opened a tab so my mom bought us drinks as well. The drinks were good coming from the same BARTENDER that made mines when I arrived so time went by I ordered 2 more drinks on my mom and STEPDAD tab they were made by the same BARTENDER they were good and later I went to order my mom and myself 1 on my tab and the other BARTENDER made them so I gave my mom her drink and she was conversing with an old school friend and I went and set with my friend and I sipped my drink it was sour and as I turned looking for my mom she was at the bar asking for her drink to be fixed and was turned down disrespected and some. So I went over there asking can the other BARTENDER just remake them the glasses were still full the other BARTENDER stated we will have to charge you for new drinks I said maam they are still full she began to be sarcastic and make a scene saying they want the other good BARTENDER apparently shes better than me so I just asked for a refund on the last 2 drinks which were both full glasses and she began to ignore me so my song came up to sing I left and this stranger white guy brought me my card I was confused so when I went and asked them why would you close out my tab with a stranger a guy I never met in my life and I stood here asking to close it nicely for 10mins and as soon as I go to sing you give a total stranger my card I dont have no receipt no nothing then she states well he paid for your tab I said I dont know him I didnt ask him to pay for my tab where is my receipt because she then states that she did charge me for the 1st drinks and he paid for the other drinks she didnt give me no receipt I called the police they were racist as was the security at the bar I will be taking this to court as bad as identity theft is in the world today they couldnt even apologize about giving my card to a total stranger which happen to be a white man they thinking just because Im a black woman Im supposed to be ok with this stranger paying for my drinks and getting my credit card no Im furious and disturbed that they thought I would be happy I can pay for my own drinks and futher more my husband who wasnt present wouldnt appreciate me taking money from another man who is a stranger I will never go back here.
